There was another great feſtival celebrated by the Greeks at PLATAEA, in honour of JUPITER ELEUTHERIUS;


the aſſembly was compoſed of delegates from almoſt all the cities of GREECE; and the rites which were inſtituted in honour of JUPITER, as the guardian of


LIBERTY, were performed with the utmoſt magnificence and ſolemn pomp.
